This paper discusses the design and performance evaluation of epidemic routing protocols for intermittently connected networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of buffer occupancy and data delivery reliability, which are related to data structures and algorithms, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category. The paper also involves information theory and cryptography, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed protocols, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
